docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:1:# FARM RX — BUILD HANDOFF
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:2:### A customer-facing farm management platform, by Crop RX Solutions
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:6:- **Product name:** Farm Rx
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:19:The user is a 55-year-old farmer, in a truck, in July sun, possibly with gloves on, possibly without his reading glasses. He is *not* tech-savvy and he will abandon this app the first time it confuses him.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:26:Farm Rx is Crop RX-branded, but a farmer's grain position is the most private number on his farm. If the software is named after his chemical supplier, he will quietly wonder whether his supplier can see what he made. Kill that doubt explicitly:
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:28:- An explicit per-farm toggle: **"Share my grain position with my Crop RX rep — OFF."**
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:46:No App Store review, no Apple developer account, no 30% cut, **instant updates** (critical when fixing a bug during planting), one codebase, installable to the home screen with the ℞ icon, works offline in bad cell coverage. iOS supports Web Push for installed PWAs, so alerts work. Wrap in Capacitor later *only if* app-store presence becomes necessary. **Mobile-first is not a nice-to-have — most sessions will be on a phone.**
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:52:Every table is farm-scoped. A Crop RX rep sees a farm's private data **only** if that farm flipped the share toggle. Mason's prior CRX Manager audits surfaced RLS holes — treat this as a known risk area and get the policies independently reviewed before any customer touches it.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:69:- **identity-preserved delivery requirements** (segregated bins, segregated trucks).
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:79:Build in this order. **Do not build them all at once — that is how farm software projects die.**
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:90:- **Field** — name, location/legal description, total acres, FSA farm/tract number (optional), soil productivity index (optional).
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:97:- **Entity** — fields roll up to an operating entity. Mason runs several (Wells Farm Group, Next Generation Farms, etc.). Support multiple entities per user and **filter every report by entity.**
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:107:**This is the module that makes farmers log in daily. It is the reason the product exists. A dedicated, well-built page.**
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:112:- → **expected bushels** per crop, per entity, per whole farm.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:121:The marketing plan, % sold, and breakevens **recalculate against whichever is live.** Pre-harvest the farmer markets against projected; at harvest he flips to actual and everything downstream updates.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:129:- **Local cash bids:** nearest elevators by farm ZIP — elevator name, cash price, basis, delivery window.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:131:- Cache server-side. Never call the API per page load.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:143:The single sentence a farmer should be able to read in two seconds:
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:158:- Farmer sets a plan: *"sell 10% at $4.80, another 10% at $5.00, 20% by Sept 1."*
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:165:Overlay it on the position view. Without it a farmer marketing against breakeven alone is seeing half the picture. This is what separates a real marketing tool from a spreadsheet.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:168:- Bushels in each bin. On-farm vs. commercial storage.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:177:WASDE, Grain Stocks, Prospective Plantings, Crop Progress. Farmers plan marketing around these dates. Simple calendar + optional reminder. USDA publishes the schedule publicly.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:180:Farm Rx shows **numbers and the farmer's own targets.** It never says "sell now." Both Bushel and Harvest Profit are explicit that they do not offer marketing advice. Add a plain-language disclaimer on the Grain and Profitability pages. **Mason is not a licensed advisor and the product must not imply otherwise.**
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:186:**Port and simplify from CRX Manager.** Farmers abandon complex inventory tools — keep this lean.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:190:- **Two sources:** (a) delivered by Crop RX, (b) **added by the farmer himself** (bought elsewhere). Both tracked.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:191:- Tracking the farmer's *whole shed* — not just CRX purchases — is exactly what makes this a real compliance tool rather than a sales gimmick. Mirror CRX Manager's approach.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:194:Eventually: a delivery entered in CRX Manager **auto-appears** in that customer's Farm Rx inventory. Design the schema now so this drops in cleanly — shared product IDs, a delivery-event table. **Do not build the sync in v1. Do not block it either.**
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:197:Log applications: product(s), rate, **EPA reg #**, date, field, applicator, target pest, weather at application, REI/PHI. Pull product + EPA reg data from the inventory item so the farmer never retypes a reg number. Reuse the compliance-record structure from CRX Manager.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:200:- Given fields + planned programs → **how much product is needed to cover the farm.**
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:215:A dedicated page. This produces the artifact a farmer hands his banker and his landlord.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:229:Side by side, one screen. Reads arrangement definitions from Fields. This is what farmers use to evaluate a lease and negotiate with a landlord.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:232:- Per crop, per field, per whole farm.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:245:This one visual is worth more to a farmer than ten reports. Make it the memorable thing about the page.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:248:Falls out of this module nearly free — and most farmers genuinely do not know which fields make money and which ones bleed. **This is the number that changes what they're willing to cash-rent.** Surface it prominently.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:261:- **Service intervals** with reminders (oil change, filters, DEF, inspections) — reminders push to the Task Board (Module 6).
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:277:- Reminders / notifications (in-app + email).
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:282:Keep it dead simple. This is a farm crew, not a software team. No sprints, no story points, no swimlanes.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:288:Farmers must be able to bring in **planting and harvest data** from **Climate FieldView, John Deere Operations Center, and AgFiniti (Ag Leader).**
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:303:- **Phase A (v1):** **File upload.** The farmer exports a shapefile/CSV from FieldView, Ops Center, or AgFiniti and uploads it. Works immediately. Zero partnerships, zero approvals, zero OAuth. **Ship this.**
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:309:- Hybrid/variety by field — **auto-populated from planter as-planted data**, or **manually tagged** if the farmer has no monitor.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:310:- Link **variety → field → yield** so the farmer can answer *"what did that hybrid actually make on that ground?"*
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:345:1. **v1:** Free/cheap futures API + **manual basis entry** (farmer types his local bid once). Ships now, costs nothing, proves the product.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:349:**Hard gate before building the cash-bid feed:** confirm **in writing** with Barchart that their license permits displaying elevator cash bids to end-user farmers inside a commercial application. *(This is a real legal question — get it confirmed by Barchart, and ideally by counsel, before committing dev time.)*
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:370:                        farmers tune red out within a week and miss the one that mattered.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:380:- **The farm's own logo goes TOP-LEFT** in the sidebar. This is *their* software.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:382:- If the farm uploads no logo, **fall back to their farm name in bold.** Never leave the slot empty.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:383:- **The login screen is the one place to go full CRX brand:** large ℞ / "Farm Rx" mark, CRX green, the slogan, and *"by Crop RX Solutions."* The instant they log in, it becomes their farm and Crop RX steps back to a footer mark.
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:386:**A working HTML mockup** (dashboard + login, real tokens, real logo, co-branding lockup, stat boxes, alert card, data table, total bar) accompanies this handoff — use it as the visual reference. *Note: the mockup file is labeled "Rx One"; the name is now **Farm Rx**. All tokens and layout still apply.*
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:418:- CRX Manager → Farm Rx delivery sync
docs/farm-rx-handoff.md:428:2. **Prepay balance tracking** — Crop RX already processes prepay invoices, and farmers prepay for tax reasons. Showing a prepay balance and what it's drawn against ties Farm Rx to the invoicing. In or out?

 succeeded in 461ms:
